The paper describes the use of neural networks to automate the analysis of sleep stages for the diagnosis of sleep disorders. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks to produce a hypnodensity graph, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the validation of the accuracy of sleep stage scoring, which involves statistical analysis and optimization of the neural network model (cs.LG, cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the potential for home sleep studies, which involves human-computer interaction and human factors (cs.HC).
